      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust 2005 Porsche 911 Carrera S (997.1) featuring the M97.01 3.8L flat-six powerplant equipped with VarioCam Plus. This specimen retains its factory-spec Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) for adaptive damping and a G97 6-speed manual transaxle that delivers precise, tactile shift throws. The IMS bearing has been inspected and the rear main seal replaced, addressing key platform concerns. Deceleration is handled by four-piston monoblock aluminum calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing no signs of significant thermal distress. The chassis geometry remains within factory tolerances with negligible bushing deflection, ensuring the communicative steering feel synonymous with the 911 lineage. This is a driver-focused example maintained for optimal kinetic performance.",
